menu "Node A Configuration"

    config USE_MOCK_SENSORS
        bool "Use mock sensor data (no real hardware)"
        default y
        help
            Enable this to use simulated sensor readings instead of
            real I2C/GPIO hardware. Useful for testing firmware logic
            before sensor parts arrive.

    config SENSOR_SAMPLE_INTERVAL_MS
        int "Sensor sampling interval (milliseconds)"
        default 30000
        range 1000 300000
        help
            How often the sensor task reads and transmits data.
            Default is 30 seconds (30000 ms).
            In deep-sleep mode, this is the timer wakeup period.

    config HEALTH_REPORT_INTERVAL_MS
        int "Health report interval (milliseconds)"
        default 120000
        range 5000 600000
        help
            How often the health task reports device diagnostics.
            Default is 120 seconds (120000 ms).

    config NODE_ALWAYS_ON_RELAY
        bool "Always-on relay mode (disable deep sleep)"
        default n
        help
            When enabled, the node stays awake with the radio on so it
            can relay mesh traffic for other nodes. The sensor loop uses
            vTaskDelay instead of deep sleep.

            When disabled (default), the node enters ESP32 deep sleep
            between sensor readings to save power. It wakes via a timer
            (CONFIG_SENSOR_SAMPLE_INTERVAL_MS) or PIR motion interrupt.

    config PIR_GPIO_PIN
        int "PIR sensor GPIO pin number"
        default 25
        range 0 39
        help
            GPIO pin connected to the PIR motion sensor digital output.
            Must be an RTC-capable GPIO for deep-sleep ext1 wakeup.
            Default is GPIO 25.

endmenu
